<DOC><DOCNO> SJMN91-06168235 </DOCNO><ACCESS> 06168235 </ACCESS><CAPTION>  Photos (3); PHOTO: Polonia; PHOTO: Jackson; PHOTO: Kelly  </CAPTION><DESCRIPT>  PROFESSIONAL; BASEBALL; BRIEF  </DESCRIPT><LEADPARA>  Outfielder Luis Polonia has declared war on Angels fans. Polonia was upsetbecause fans at Anaheim Stadium booed him Monday when he lost two easyflyballs in the lights, then cheered when he managed to haul in another gimme.He tipped his cap and told reporters afterward he won't sign autographsanymore.;    Nevertheless, Angels Manager Doug Rader was ready to pin a medalon Polonia: &quot;For staying out there and taking it, Luis Polonia is as big a manas lives in this state.&quot;  </LEADPARA><SECTION>  Sports  </SECTION><HEADLINE>  TO CATCH A FLY  </HEADLINE><MEMO>  Hit andamp; Run  </MEMO><TEXT>     We never realized getting paid $330,000 a year to catch flies was suchhazardous duty.;  TAKING THE REINS; Manager Tom Kelly's Minnesota Twins mightnot have enough horses to stay with the A's all season, but he does have onereal thoroughbred. Kelly owns 4-year-old filly Albell in a partnership.;   Albell runs at Canterbury Downs in Minnesota, and she has won three timessince the group purchased her last year.;    &quot;He's (Kelly) very professionaland good to work with,&quot; said Linda Taliaferra, the horse's trainer. &quot;Heunderstands the game -- he compares it to baseball in that you have to havethe horses in your barn to win, just as you have to have the players in yourdugout.&quot;;  VINCENT KNOWS; He can be seen sitting on the edge of the ChicagoWhite Sox dugout sometimes, looking strangely idle. But Bo Jackson insistshe'll return from his hip ailment.;    &quot;Confident is probably one of themost-used words in my vocabulary,&quot; he said. &quot;And even if I don't play thisyear, I've got the next two seasons to enjoy with the White Sox.&quot;;    Jacksonevidently has had too much time to think as he recovers.;    &quot;Once I do getback, I'll be a totally different Bo Jackson,&quot; he said. &quot;I may start using'Vincent' and just drop the 'Bo.' I may shave my head. Who knows?&quot;  </TEXT><COUNTRY>  USA  </COUNTRY><EDITION>  Morning Final  </EDITION><CODE>  SJ  </CODE><NAME>  San Jose Mercury News  </NAME><PUBDATE>   910616  </PUBDATE> <DAY>  Sunday  </DAY><MONTH>  June  </MONTH><PG.COL>  8D  </PG.COL><PUBYEAR>  1991  </PUBYEAR><REGION>  WEST  </REGION><FEATURE>  PHOTO  </FEATURE><STATE>  CA  </STATE><WORD.CT>  322  </WORD.CT><DATELINE>  Sunday June 16, 199100168235,SJ1  </DATELINE><COPYRGHT>  Copyright 1991, San Jose Mercury News  </COPYRGHT><LIMLEN>  1  </LIMLEN><LANGUAGE>  ENG  </LANGUAGE></DOC>